The paper deals with the optimization problem of Radial Basis Function Neural Networks (RBFNNs), which is a topic related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of canonical duality theory, which is a mathematical optimization technique, making cs.IT (Information Theory) a possible sub-category. Additionally, the paper presents applications of RBFNNs, which can be related to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SI (Signal and Image Processing).
